# Multi-Agent Research Assistant - Environment Variables
#
# This is a pointer file for Docker Compose setup.
# The actual environment variables are configured in backend/.env
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env
# 2. Fill in your API keys in backend/.env
# 3. Run: docker-compose up
#
# No frontend environment file needed - frontend uses EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL
# which is configured in docker-compose.yml

# See backend/.env.example for the complete list of required variables:
# - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (Claude Sonnet 4)
# - OPENAI_API_KEY (Embeddings)
# - LANGCHAIN_API_KEY (LangSmith tracing)
# - SUPABASE_URL
# - SUPABASE_KEY
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

# For manual (non-Docker) setup, see SETUP.md
